article.description: Kayla Tetschlag scored 16 of her 20 points in the first half and Wisconsin-Green Bay (No. 13 ESPN/USA Today, No. 17 AP) finished off a perfect home schedule with a 93-57 win over Butler on Saturday.
article.headline: Wisconsin-Green Bay improves to 27-1 overall
article.linkText: Green Bay rips Butler, goes unbeaten at home
article.story:
GREEN BAY, Wis. -- Kayla Tetschlag scored 16 of her 20 points in the first half and Wisconsin-Green Bay (No. 13 ESPN/USA Today, No. 17 AP) finished off a perfect home schedule with a 93-57 win over Butler on Saturday.

The Phoenix (27-1, 16-0 Horizon League) may have saved its performance of the season for the Bulldogs, setting season highs in points and field-goal shooting at 64.2 percent.

Butler stayed close to the Phoenix for most of the first half, but Green Bay went on a 10-0 spurt over the final 1:42 to open up a 41-23 lead at the break.

Green Bay kept the pressure on in the second half. The Phoenix hit eight of their first nine shots after the break and led by as many as 42.

Brittany Bowen led the Bulldogs (17-12, 11-6) with 19 points.
